<HEADLINE>
<P>
SKELETONS OF 30 MONKS, BABY FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The skeletons of 30 medieval monks have been uncovered during building work to 
extend London's underground rail system, archeologists said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The graves were found on the site of an ancient monastery, St Mary's Abbey. 
All contained male adults, except for one 18-month-old baby. 
</P>
<P>
 "The baby was quite a surprise, but we will never know why it was buried with 
the monks," said Pat Wilkinson, an archeologist. 
</P>
<P>
 It has not yet been decided if the bones will be reburied or put in a museum. 
</P>
<P>
 Archeologists have until July 5 to complete the excavations before the site is 
permanently destroyed by construction work. The abbey was founded in 1135, but 
the graves date from the 15th Century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
