 The national media had initially portrayed the incident as a symbol of 
violence in the United States -- a combat veteran who was felled by a random 
drive-by shooting just days after returning from the Persian Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
 Riggs had collected $150,000 in life insurance money after her husband's 
death. 
