ROBERT ARMBRUSTER; CONDUCTOR, COMPOSER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Armbruster, 97, conductor, composer and concert pianist. A child 
prodigy, John Robert Sommers Armbruster began performing professionally at age 
8 in his native Philadelphia.He moved to California as a young man and led the 
Robert Armbruster Orchestra for NBC radio, performing on such popular shows as 
the "Chase & Sanborn Hour." He later served for many years as head of recording 
film scores for MGM. Armbruster was a popular guest conductor at the Hollywood 
Bowl. On Monday in Santa Monica. 
</P>
