<HEADLINE>
<P>
NITTY-GRITTY: INSIDE & OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Welcome summer. Roll up rugs and expose bare floors for a cooler look; replace 
heavy draperies with lace curtains; substitute artwork with flowery prints; 
cover toss pillows in bright chintz or crisp awning stripes. 
</P>
<P>
 * After grilling outdoors, clean the grids while they are still warm to make 
the task easier. Scrape clean with a wire brush or rub with crumpled foil. Wash 
grease off with soapy water; rinse and dry. 
</P>
<P>
 * When using a caulking gun, make a straight line by using two strips of 
1/2-inch-wide masking tape that are placed 1/8-inch apart over the area to be 
sealed. Apply the caulking along the center crack and even out with a moist 
finger. 
</P>
<P>
 * Scrub grout between tiles with undiluted vinegar and a toothbrush. 
</P>
<P>
 * Remove stains from marble with lemon juice or vinegar. Rub discolored area 
briefly because marble can become discolored with prolonged rubbing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Keep baby bottles from falling over in refrigerator. Fill a six-pack 
cardboard carton with a day's supply of prepared bottles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
