WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; POWER FAILURE AFFECTS TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An underground cable failure knocked out electrical power for about an hour 
and a half in portions of Port Hueneme Friday evening, shutting down stoplights 
at two major intersections during peak-hour traffic, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Power went out at about 5 p.m., causing traffic to back up at Channel Islands 
Boulevard and Victoria Avenue.  
</P>
<P>
 The power failure also caused traffic delays of about two blocks at Pleasant 
Valley and Ventura roads, Port Hueneme police said. 
</P>
<P>
 No accidents were reported at either intersection. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials with Southern California Edison said about 3,500 customers were 
without power. TRACY WILSON 
