<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN IS SHOT AT HOME IN ROBBERY ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-old Ventura man was shot during an attempted robbery at his house 
early Friday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Alvaro Ponce-Hernandez was listed in fair condition at Ventura County 
Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 He was sleeping at a house he shares with three men when they were awakened 
shortly after midnight by three armed robbers at the door, said Detective Jerry 
Thurston of the Ventura Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers forced their way into the house in the 200 block of Vince Street 
after one of the men answered the door, Thurston said. The armed trio then 
grabbed the teen-aged son of one resident, Alfredo Ponce Villa Gomez, and 
threatened to shoot him unless Gomez gave them money, Thurston said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gomez, who was later arrested for possessing cocaine for sale, threw some cash 
at the robbers, Thurston said. During the confusion, Ponce-Hernandez made a 
movement that startled one of the robbers, who shot him in the neck. 
</P>
<P>
 The attackers fled and Ponce-Hernandez was taken to Ventura County Medical 
Center. Investigators are still looking for the robbers. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
