<P>
 UNLV, faced with a $10.5-million deficit, may reconsider joining the Western 
Athletic Conference because of a $600,000 admission fee. 
</P>
<P>
 University regents voted to approve admission to the league on the condition 
that the conference drop the fee. 
</P>
<P>
 The city prosecutor's office said in Columbus, Ohio, that it will not file 
charges against two Ohio State basketball players accused of assault and the 
firing of a gun during a disturbance. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniel Smith, a former roommate of Buckeye guard Greg Simpson, told police 
that Simpson, forward Charles Macon and another person threw bricks at him in 
his apartment on June 9. Smith told police he heard two to three gunshots as he 
fled. 
</P>
<P>
 Rob Levering, an assistant city prosecutor, said his office did not plan to 
file charges because it was unable to substantiate the police report. 
</P>
