<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR 2 COMMISSIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city clerk is asking residents to apply for vacancies on the Planning 
Commission and the Transportation and Parking Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 There is currently one opening on the Planning Commission and three spots 
available on the Transportation and Parking Commission.Those appointed to fill 
the vacancies will serve three-year terms. 
</P>
<P>
 Planning commissioners review developers' construction plans and make 
decisions involving land use in the city. This commission advises City Council 
members how they should proceed on each project. 
</P>
<P>
 The Transportation and Parking Commission reviews proposed roadway 
improvements and makes recommendations to the council on transportation policy 
and parking programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested can pick up an application at the city clerk's office, 613 E. 
Broadway, Room 110. The filing deadline for all vacancies is July 6. JENNIFER 
OLDHAM 
</P>
