<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: 14 RECEIVE $972 FINES IN COCKFIGHTING CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fourteen men arrested last month at a Panorama City cockfight were fined $972 
each and placed on three years probation Thursday after pleading no contest to 
charges they participated in cockfighting. 
</P>
<P>
 A 15th defendant entered his plea Monday, said Rick Schmidt of the city 
attorney's office.Municipal Judge Alan Ellis barred the men from possessing 
roosters or cockfighting paraphernalia while they are on probation. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors disturbed by noise summoned police May 29 to a house in the 8300 
block of Ranchito Avenue, where officers from the Los Angeles Police 
Department's Van Nuys Division found men counting money and a cockfight in 
progress in the garage. 
</P>
<P>
 Police also found 15 fighting cocks, including two that were seriously 
injured. Two other roosters already were dead. Fighting spurs, energy-enhancing 
drugs for the roosters, ankle ties and several firearms also were seized. 
</P>
<P>
 The city attorney's office identified the men as Simplicio Vargas, 31, the 
owner of the house; Ramon Castro, 40, of Arcadia; Gem Famatid, 41, and Josifino 
Guerarra, 58, of Carson; Marcelina Montero, 43, of Lake View Terrace; Nonito 
Jucaban, 44, of North Hills; Abelandor Valera, 44, of Granada Hills; Fred 
Palafox, 55, and Jun Dairo, 27, of Inglewood; John Belmundo, 23 of Burbank; 
Asterio Valera, 42, of West Hills; Macario Tadena, 33, of Arleta; and Melbert 
Tato, 18; Richardo Pasiliao, 43, and Enrique Paragas, 42, of Panorama City.  
</P>
<P>
 The roosters were turned over to the city's Department of Animal Regulation. 
ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
