SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 2 INJURED IN FREEWAY ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man whose car crashed on the Golden State Freeway and seriously injured a 
passenger has been booked on suspicion of driving while intoxicated, police 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mauricio Gonzales, 24, of San Fernando lost control of his car near Pyramid 
Lake on Thursday evening, according to police.Gonzales was treated at Henry 
Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital, according to the CHP. 
</P>
<P>
 Carmen Curtis, 20, of San Fernando was thrown from the automobile, police 
said. Curtis was taken by helicopter to Henry Mayo and transferred Friday to 
Kaiser Permanente Medical Center in Panorama City. She was listed in fair 
condition with a separated right shoulder and lacerations to her hands and 
ankles, Kaiser spokeswoman Jessica Lott said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither adult was wearing a seat belt, said Officer Ben Dibene of the 
California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 A 3-year-old girl and 4-year-old boy in the back seat were not injured, the 
officer added. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't know how these kids survived because they weren't wearing seat belts 
either," Dibene said. 
</P>
