SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MOTORIST HITS EMBANKMENT, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Lancaster man died Friday morning after driving off the Antelope Valley 
Freeway into an embankment where his car overturned, a California Highway 
Patrol officer said. 
</P>
<P>
 Curtis Sullivan, 38, lost control of his 1989 Nissan Stanza about 5 a.m. on 
the southbound side of the freeway just north of Agua Dulce Canyon Road, said 
CHP Officer Ben Dibene. 
</P>
<P>
 "For unknown reasons, he veered to the right and veered off the road, crashed 
through a guard rail, went down the embankment and overturned," Dibene said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sullivan was driving about 65 m.p.h. and was wearing a seat belt when the 
collision occurred, Dibene said. There were no other passengers in the car. 
</P>
<P>
 Sullivan died at the scene. 
