<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; TODAY'S GAMES AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GROUP F 
</P>
<P>
 at Florida Citrus Bowl, Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 Belgium vs. Netherlands 
</P>
<P>
 * TIME: 9:30 a.m. PDT. 
</P>
<P>
 * TV: ABC, Univision. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY MATCHUPS: Belgian Coach Paul Van Himst will use three forwards instead 
of two, guaranteeing a defensive mind-set.It's the only way he believes his 
team can play in hot, humid weather, which continues to drain energy and 
dictates a slower pace. Josip Weber, Belgium's scoring threat, did little last 
Sunday against Morocco. He and Marc Degryse, who scored Belgium's only goal, 
will be the forwards today. Dutch Coach Dick Advocaat's team is 
offense-oriented. Advocaat probably will make one change, starting forward 
Gaston Taument in place of Marc Overmars. Taument scored the game-winner in 
Holland's 2-1 decision over Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: Belgium will be a slave to defense, taking few chances and waiting 
for counterattacks. Holland will attack, but this game won't be an offensive 
display because neither team is accustomed to this weather. Look for the Dutch 
to use their speed on the wings and try to get the ball to Dennis Bergkamp.  
</P>
<P>
 * OUTCOME: Because both won their first games, neither team is in a must-win 
situation. However, neither particularly wants to win the group title, because 
that would mean a game against the second-place finisher in tough Group E in 
Orlando. Second place brings an easier foe, the runner-up in Group B. That will 
probably be Cameroon, Sweden or Russia. Look for a 1-1 tie. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
