<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; TODAY'S GAMES AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GROUP D 
</P>
<P>
 at Foxboro Stadium, Foxboro, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
 Argentina vs. Nigeria 
</P>
<P>
 * TIME: 1 p.m. PDT. 
</P>
<P>
 * TV: ABC, Univision. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY MATCHUPS: One of the more intriguing pairings in Round 1, pitting 
venerable World Cup warriors against an emerging soccer nation.Argentina has 
won two World Cups and reached the final on two other occasions, most recently 
four years ago. This is Nigeria's first World Cup. For openers, Argentina 
crushed Greece, 4-0, and the Super Eagles handled Bulgaria with ease, 3-0. It 
will be interesting to see how the Nigerians defend the Argentine stars, 
notably Diego Maradona, Claudio Caniggia and Gabriel Batistuta. Batistuta 
scored three times against Greece, Maradona once. Nigeria has an excellent 
defender in Uche Okechukwu, who took Bulgarian star Hristo Stoichkov out of the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: In one game, Argentina has done much to repair its image as a World 
Cup dinosaur in need of an overhaul. In one game, Maradona has dispelled 
notions is finished. Conversely, Nigeria has proved it is worthy of 
considerable pre-tournament hype. Both should emerge from the group and be 
factors in the knockout round. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTCOME: This is the classic youth-vs.- experience matchup. Experience 
usually wins. Greek players were awe-struck in the presence of their Argentine 
heroes. Nigeria has much more talent than Greece but might also be overcome by 
the moment. Argentina wins, 3-2. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
