<P>
 John Aldridge, who entered the game against Mexico in the second half and 
scored Ireland's only goal Friday, almost didn't make it onto the field. 
</P>
<P>
 A FIFA official, apparently confused because Ireland was making two 
substitutions, grabbed Aldridge and tried to keep him from going onto the 
field. After some shouting, Aldridge simply took his place. 
</P>
