WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; NOT ENOUGH SHAIBUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 They're not booing, they're yelling Shaibu! Shaibu! or the Russian chant for 
"Score! Score!" 
</P>
<P>
 Or, at least a loose interpretation. Shaibu , pronounced Sha-boo, actually 
means "Puck," and is the verbiage used to cheer on Mother Russia's hockey 
teams. The 200 or so Russian fans who followed their team to the Silverdome, 
where the Russians lost, 3-1, to Sweden on Friday, use the same exclamation for 
soccer. 
</P>
<P>
 Seems to be a shortage of everything in Russia. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
