<TEXT>
<P>
 Minutes after Italy beat Norway, 1-0, around midnight, Italy time, Thursday, 
city streets all over the country were crowded with hooting, screaming, 
triumphant Italians. Even tourists got caught up in the moment when jubilant 
locals threw themselves into baroque fountains in central Rome. Embarrassed 
Japanese and German tourists were persuaded to shout and cheer along with the 
best of them. 
