<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; PERSONNEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Franco Baresi, the Italian captain, faces knee surgery after being injured in 
the first half of a 1-0 victory over Norway on Thursday and will be out for the 
rest of the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 German midfielder Andy Moeller, anticipated as being one of the stars of the 
World Cup, might be dropped from the world champions' lineup for their last 
Group C match against South Korea at Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
 Moeller has failed to live up to expectations and Coach Berti Vogts said 
Friday that Moeller, 26, seemed to be afraid of contact. 
</P>
<P>
 Italian star Roberto Baggio was still struggling with being replaced 21 
minutes into Thursday's game against Norway, saying Friday, "I asked (Coach 
Arrigo Sacchi) if he would have taken Maradona off in the same situation. He 
said yes, but I think Maradona would have played the whole game." 
</P>
