WEEKEND TV; TOP TOPICS: CIVIL WAR, DOMESTIC VIOLENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N. F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Civil War is fought on two fronts this weekend, starting with TNT's 
presentation of the two-part drama "Gettysburg," which was released in theaters 
last year. Martin Sheen, Tom Berenger, Jeff Daniels and Sam Elliott star, 
Sunday at 5 and 8 p.m. Part 2 airs Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Ken Burns' chronicle "The Civil War," a 1990 documentary, begins Sunday 
at 8 p.m. on KCET-TV Channel 28 and KPBS-TV Channel 15, and at 7 p.m. on 
KVCR-TV Channel 24. 
</P>
<P>
 Domestic violence and the O. J. Simpson case will be the topics on many of the 
public service programs. 
</P>
<P>
 In sports, the United States plays Romania on Sunday in a World Cup soccer 
game at the Rose Bowl at 1 p.m. on ABC and KMEX-TV. N. F. MENDOZA 
