<P>
RUOTOLO ROLLS 7 TO LEAD SPLASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Raffaele Ruotolo scored four goals and had three assists to lead the Splash to 
a 9-7 victory over Monterrey on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory gives the Splash (6-0) the Continental Indoor Soccer League's best 
record and matches last season's victory total by the franchise, when it was 
the Los Angeles United.It has a 2 1/2-game lead in the Western Division. 
</P>
<P>
 Monterrey (2-4), with its small field and boisterous fans, was expected to 
provide the Splash with its most difficult challenge on the four-game trip. 
</P>
<P>
 The Splash took a 4-0 lead before La Raza tied the score, 5-5, early in the 
third quarter. Ruotolo made it 6-5, then assisted Sam George 2 minutes 21 
seconds into the fourth quarter to make it 7-6. Ruotolo provided the margin of 
victory with his fourth goal to put the Splash up, 8-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Armando Valdivia scored twice, and Doug Neely and Rod Castro also scored. 
</P>
