<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: CROWLEY GIVEN PERMANENT POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dean Crowley, acting Southern Section commissioner since October, was named to 
the permanent post Friday, the section announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The Southern Section Executive Committee appointed Crowley, 60, during a 
meeting at the section office in Cerritos.Crowley, who has been an associate 
commissioner of athletics since 1987, is only the seventh commissioner in the 
organization's 81 years. 
</P>
<P>
 He was named acting commissioner by the executive committee when Stan Thomas, 
the former commissioner, was forced to resign Oct. 13 after an investigation 
revealed he abused his expense account. Thomas became commissioner in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ron Prettyman, Southern California College athletic director, announced two 
additions to the school's athletic department. 
</P>
<P>
 Randy Hawkins has been hired as an assistant women's basketball coach. 
Formerly an assistant with the men's team, Hawkins, an SCC alumnus, returns to 
coaching after resigning two years ago to spend more time with his family. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Dahlgren, also an SCC alumnus, has been hired as an assistant baseball 
coach. Dahlgren was an assistant baseball coach at University High the last two 
seasons. Signings 
</P>
<P>
 Derek Fahs, formerly of Fountain Valley High and Cal State Fullerton, has 
signed a free-agent contract with the Erie (Pa.) Sailors, his family said.  
</P>
<P>
 Fahs, a right-hander who was selected all-county by The Times in 1991, will be 
a starting pitcher for the independent Class-A team. At Fullerton, Fahs, 21, 
started and relieved. 
</P>
<P>
 Amber Chaney, a guard from Garland, Tex., has signed a letter of intent with 
the Southern California College women's basketball team, Coach Dean Cooper 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaney, 5 feet 8, averaged 18.2 points as a senior last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Maynard, MVP of the Canyon boys' soccer team, has signed a letter of 
intent with Duke, boys' Athletic Director Steve Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Maynard led the Comanches in scoring and was selected All-Century League. 
</P>
