<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEEN KILLS GIRLFRIEND, 14, THEN HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THUAN LE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-ager shot and killed his pregnant, 14-year-old girlfriend Friday night 
and moments later shot himself to death, police said.  
</P>
<P>
 The shootings occurred just before 7:45 p.m. in the 3300 block of South Park 
Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosa Vargas and the 16-year-old boy had been dating since the beginning of the 
year, and she was three months' pregnant with his child, her sister Betty 
Vargas, 18, said Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of his temper, Rosa Vargas heeded her mother's advice and broke up 
with the boy a week ago, Betty Vargas said.  
</P>
<P>
 On Friday night, the boy and a friend arrived on their bicycles at Rosa's 
house to return some of her belongings and to get his belongings from her, the 
sister said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was drunk," said Rosa's brother Frank, 20. "He was always drunk." 
</P>
<P>
 As they all stood on the front yard, he asked Rosa if the baby was his, Betty 
Vargas said. Her mother responded that he need not worry about it. At that 
point, Vargas said, he pulled a gun and shot at the mother, putting a bullet in 
the wall.  
</P>
<P>
 She ran inside, and he began shooting at Rosa, hitting her in the arm and 
neck, Vargas said. She staggered to the door and collapsed and died just 
outside of it. 
</P>
<P>
 He then ran down the street, stopping a few houses away and shooting himself 
to death. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not released the boy's name. 
</P>
<P>
 "She was looking forward to having her baby," Vargas said. "Rosa was a sweet 
girl with long hair down to her back. I can't believe he killed my sister." 
</P>
<P>
 Rosa was a freshman at Saddleback High School. The shooter went to Horizon 
High School, Vargas said. 
</P>
