<P>
POLICE INVESTIGATING TEEN'S DEATH AS POSSIBLE HOMICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Investigators have still not determined if a 17-year-old who died from a 
gunshot wound to the head shot himself while playing with a handgun or was shot 
by someone else, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of Quy Tung Nguyen of Westminster was found Thursday afternoon inside 
an apartment in the 13700 block of Edwards Street by officers investigating 
reports of gunfire, Sgt. Mike Mittelstaedt said. 
</P>
<P>
 "There were people inside of the living room passing the gun around and 
playing with it," Mittelstaedt said. "The victim suffered a head wound and the 
gun was found underneath his body. But we have not proved that he did it to 
himself so we are handling it like a homicide." 
</P>
<P>
 Immediately after the shooting, two young men were seen running out of the 
apartment, witnesses told police. They were later tracked down by investigators 
and are not considered suspects, the sergeant said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are witnesses, not suspects," Mittelstaedt said. "Apparently, each had 
their reasons for not wanting to be there after the shooting. One was on 
probation." 
</P>
<P>
 Neither the victim nor the two who ran from the apartment lived there. The 
female occupant of the apartment was in the shower when the shooting occurred 
and called police after hearing a gunshot, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's up to us to prove one way or another," Mittelstaedt said. "We haven't 
proven that it was a homicide. But it's looking more and more like the deceased 
did it to himself." 
</P>
</TEXT>
